list-item.p:
Taking care of the domestic and international security of society by


developing and maintaining domestic security forces, programs for their activities, and guiding those activities;

developing and maintaining national armed forces, programs for their activities, and guiding those activities;

entering and maintaining international economic, political, and military alliances in order to achieve and preserve the international security of the country; and

taking the necessary measures for protection of public infrastructure, information systems, life, and private property in the country.

Regulating macro-economic processes by


designing and implementing fiscal and budget policies;

designing and applying legal measures for fostering domestic and international private investments;

planning and managing public investments; and

designing and implementing economic diplomacy.

Supporting the reproduction of the human resources in the country by


developing and maintaining the educational system;

developing and maintaining the health care system;

administering various social policies;

supporting science and cultural life; and

supporting sport and recreation institutions and activities.
